A ranar Laraba, Shugaba Donald Trump ya yi tsokaci kan talla da China Daily ta biya a cikin Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi yawan masu wallafa a Iowa - bayan da ya zargi China da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters a matsayin wani sabon mataki na yakin neman Washington don matsa lamba kan China.
Yayin da gwamnatocin kasashen waje ke tallata tallace-tallace don inganta cinikayya, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin cinikayya mai tsanani wanda ya ga sun daidaita haraji ga abubuwan da suka shigo da su.
Da farko dai, an yi niyyar sanya wa China harajin ramuwar gayya a farkon yakin cinikayya don a ci zarafin masu fitar da kayayyaki zuwa wasu jihohi kamar Iowa, wanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, kamar yadda masana Sin da Amurka suka bayyana.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, wanda shi ne babban mai fitar da kayayyakin noma zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
China, Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani labarin ra'ayi a cikin Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi, yanzu yana ƙara yawan waɗannan abubuwan ta hanyar buga tallan talla a cikin jaridunmu kyauta.
Game da yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin China tana amfani da ƙaunataccen al'adun Amurka na 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma 'yan jarida ta hanyar sanya talla a cikin Des Moines Register, in ji Branstad.
"A bangarensa, a cikin "taro a kan titi a nan Beijing za ku ga 'yan murya kaɗan ne masu nuna bambanci kuma ba za ku ga ainihin abin da ke nuna ra'ayoyi daban-daban da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya samu game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta Sin", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa wani daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya ki amincewa da tayin da aka yi masa na buga labarin, ko da yake bai bayyana ko wace jarida ba ce.
